  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Formally, given a user request U j i = (u i 1, u i 2,.",
    "), the language model needs to generate a response R j i = (r i 1, r i 2,...), where u i n and r i n are the n th tokens of the i th user request and language model response, respectively.",
    "To provide in-context responses, the assistant also needs to consider the conversation context",
    "where t is the number of previous dialogue turns to consider.",
    "In goal-oriented dialogue, the users' behavior is typically captured by a closed set of intents (Budzianowski et al., 2018) and with limited leeway for topic shifts or exploratory dialogue."
  ],
